==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharisaical
<hw>Phar`i*sa"ic*al</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Pharisaicus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>Farisai:ko`s</grk>: cf. F. <ets>pharisa⟦ium⟧que</ets>. See
<er>Pharisee</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the
Pharisees; resembling the Pharisees.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>Pharisaic</xex> sect among the Jews.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Addicted to external forms
and ceremonies; making a show of religion without the spirit of it;
ceremonial; formal; hypocritical; self-righteous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Excess of
outward and <xex>pharisaical</xex> holiness.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Bacon.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pharisaical</xex> ostentation.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Phar`i*sa"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Phar`i*sa"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharisaism</ent>⟦br⟧
